            It is not much functionality here yet. However, you can still access to play the game, look at profile
            settings or log
            out.</b></p>
        <p style="color:gray"><b>Basically, the idea is to play ping pong tournament so that every player (human + 15 AI
            players) faces each other once.
            Human vs AI will always be the first match and human plays always on left. AI vs AI matches will be played
            using a simple function.</b></p>
        <p style="color:gray"><b>The winner of the match is the player, who reaches 11 points at first. However there
            must have at least 2 point difference between
            the scores of the winner and the loser.</b></p>
        <p style="color:gray"><b>The tournament points will be granted with following criteria: 3 points for winning a
            match with 11 points (normal time). 2 points for winning a matchon overtime (a match that goes beyond 11
            points).
            1 point for losing a match on overtime. 0 points for losing a match on normal time.
          </b></p>
        <p style="color:gray"><b>The tournament ranks will be determined with following priority. Lower priority will
            only be used, if the results with the higher priority are same:
            1. Points (Pts on the tournament table); bigger is better.
            2. Ball difference (BD on the tournament table); bigger is better.
            3. Balls against (BA on the tournament table); smaller is better. This is because if a match goes overtime,
            it encourages players to win the match ASAP.
            4. Ranking before the tournament (BA on the tournament table); smaller is better. Every player will have own
            initial rank (1-16).
          </b></p>
        <p style="color:gray"><b>Abbreviations: PLD = Games played; W = Wins; OTW, OWL = Overtime wins, loses; L =
            loses; BF, BL, BD = Balls for, against, difference;
            Pts = points.
          </b></p>
